                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>been introduced into the German synagogues<lb/> of <placeName>London</placeName>\n                since the publication of<lb/> the book. I have yet received no<lb/> orders as to\n                advertising it in the <placeName>U. S.</placeName><lb/> Jewish papers; but when you\n                again<lb/> will, please let me what a square of<lb/> 10 or 12 lines will cost for\n                one year.<lb/> I regret that only a few copies have<lb/> as yet arrived, and as many\n                as I could<lb/> spare have gone to Editors—yours among<lb/> them sent from\n                    <placeName>New York</placeName>; but I need<lb/> not add I shall be much pleased\n                to<lb/> receive subscribers names from you<lb/> until you can be supplied; or if you<lb/>\n                <hi rend=\"underline\">will send me the names I may be able</hi><lb/>\n                <hi rend=\"underline\">to send the books</hi>. The work has been<lb/> very successful\n                indeed in <placeName>England</placeName>, and<lb/> as they possess the plates I hope\n                that<lb/> if they meet with due encouragement<lb/> they will issue the book at a\n                cheaper<lb/> rate, and also a volume of the chants<lb/> which are equally fine.\n                Please bring<lb/> the book prominently before your reader<lb/> It deserves honorable\n                mention.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\"><persName>Sarah Joseph</persName> desires me to<lb/> inform you that\n                a copy of the Occident</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p38c9rq44/canvas/p2"
                }
              ]
